Simulate a solution settings object

simulate_solution_settings.Rd

This function simulates a solution settings object. It is primarily used for testing the package.

simulate_solution_settings(
  n_single_themes = 5,
  n_multi_themes = 15,
  n_weights = 5,
  lambda = 5
)

Arguments

n_single_themes

integer number of themes with a single feature to simulate. Defaults to 5.
n_multi_themes

integer number of themes with a multiple features to simulate. Defaults to 15.
n_weights

integer number of weights to simulate. Defaults to 5.
lambda

numeric lambda parameter for simulating the number of features for each theme. This parameter is used as a argument to rpois(n, lambda = lambda). Defaults to 5.

Value

A SolutionSettings object.

See also

new_solution_settings().

Examples

# simulate solution settings
x <- simulate_solution_settings(
  n_single_themes = 3, n_multi_themes = 2, n_weights = 1)

# print results
print(x)
